76561197969755028,Not Recommended,270910,17082957,"Posted: 16 July, 2015",all,The : inspector,"I bought Worms World Party Remastered because I need to own every Worms game.Worms 2 and Armageddon are my favourite Worms games and I figured since WWP was remastered it would be my new go to Worms game since it was the last of that group of games.I prefer the older style of game play rather than the new Worms games especially because of what they did to the ninja rope!I thought since they had delays releasing the game that it was going to be impressive but I was mistaken.To start off you load the game and you have the old 4:3 menus stretched to whatever screen size you have, mine is 16:9. It could be because of my graphics drivers but I don't have this issue with other games.The mouse cursor still tracks like it is on a 4:3 screen so moving up and down is normal but left and right movements of the cursor are just too fast.I have 3 screens and WWP was playing in the centre screen.Now the game menu runs in psudeo full screen which caused some issues.When you move the mouse to the left or right of the game window you actually scroll on to the other screens that arent used in the game. You try to move the cursor back to the game screen and it sometimes blocks the cursor leaving it on the unused screen.I had to move the cursor back and forth a few times and it eventually went back to the game screen. N.B. because the left and right scroll is accelerated due to the 4:3 stretch you can get the cursor to the middle screen but I actually had the cursor go from my left screen, past the WWP screen in the middle, and to my right screen because the cursor was so fast in the game screen.Starting a game is just like it used to be on the original WWP but the stretched menus just don't look nice.Once in a game it played just like it used to.The updated sounds were nice but just didn't match the graphics.The graphics are the same as the original WWP and the old soundbanks just fit better.Moving the cursor off the screen isn't a problem during a game since moving the mouse will just move the camera or weapon selection cursor.The game defaulted to my 2560x1440 graphics but the game didn't run like it was 60FPS.It was a bit choppy and just seemed dated.I quit the match changed the graphics to 1680x1050.I loaded a match and it was smooth but still looked the same as WWP back in the day.I quit WWP completely and saw that because I changed the game resolution to a lower resolution than my 2560x1440 desktop it had shifted all of my cursors that were on the lower part of the desktop up higher!Luckily I have DesktopOK running so I can just restore the icons to their original positions easily but this is just rediculous.This game was a rushed port, which is odd since they had delays, and I recommend only die hard Worms fans purchase it.I didn't try online play and only had a quick few test solo games and it plays ok in lower resolutions but the implimentation of the game seems like it's still designed for Windows 95/98 or XP.One other issue that I encountered was loading the game.If you load the game and in the part with the developer Team 17 and Tick Tock names appear you click on a different screen the game screen will minimize but you can't restore it.Alt-Tab doesn't show the game is running and I had to kill W2.exe with task manager to quit and then I reloaded the game.There's just too many issues with the game and I think it should have been redesigned for Windows 7/8/10 not just ported like this.Team 17 please release some major patches to fix everything that is broken so we can enjoy this game on our new computers without these issues."
