,Recommended,270910,17171672,"Posted: 22 July, 2015",all,CamPizza,"In my personal opinion, I think this game is getting far more negative reviews then it deserves...Not only is this the same game that I remember as a kid, but it's also the game that introduced me to the Worms franchise in the first place!So I applaud them for the fact that they even re-released this on Steam at all!Basically; what you’re getting is the same Worms World Party from 2001, but with better resolution and enhanced (optional) sound effects. Other than that, it’s practically the exact same game from when it first debut.So if you liked Worms World Party when it first came out and still enjoy it today, then I highly recommend getting it. Especially since the original disc-version I own doesn’t seem to even run on Windows 7 anymore...So while I techinically wouldn't call it a ""remastered"" game, it is still the same old fun game that I can remember."
,Recommended,270910,17309281,"Posted: 30 July, 2015",all,Lenmacca,"This is Worms World Party, just the way I remember it. It's the best Worms game ever made, and, after years of terrible Worms games and 3D, it has aged remarkably well. Running without issues on Windows 10.It's getting alot of justified criticism due to the word 'Remastered'--it shouldn't be called a remaster, rather a 'Steam edition'. It is false advertising. This is because the game has  is still in the original resolution outside the gameplay, and not much has actually been 'remastered', apart from the gameplay, which is in 1080p and a solid 60fps. It's the same game with more resolution options tacked on and Steamworks support.However, why would this matter? Of all the games, a 2D Worms game is the last one that needs to be in 1080p and 60fps. There are also new audio and sound effects, which, as a fan of the original release in 2001, I really appreciate.This is the same game that shipped in 2001, with 1080p gameplay and new audio. However, despite the false advertising, I'm still inclined to give this a positive review. This is because this is a working version of Worms World Party for modern operating systems--the old 2001 'Sold Out' version, which I still own a physical copy of, no longer works with Windows 7, nevermind Windows 10 which I recently upgraded to. I have been longing to play Worms World Party again for many years, so I am thrilled to be able to do that again.So in short, if you don't care about the false advertising and, like me, just want to play LAN or Local games of Worms World Party for nostalgic value or fun, pick it up. It was my first Worms game, and has always been my favourite, due to the amount of fond memories I have of it :)"
