,Recommended,270910,17666422,"Posted: 22 August, 2015",all,Deuterium the Sentient Mattress,"Worms World Party Remastered is, fundamentally, unchanged from its original version. Team17 seem to have misunderstood a bit what ""remastering"" actually is, meaning that this is only a ""remaster"" in a very loose sense. However, there is no denying that whilst it hasn't undergone any radical changes, the result is that this is still the same Worms World Party we know and love, for the same price as Worms Armageddon on Steam, and arguably offering a superior experience due to the new ""WormPot"" modes and the added controller support, which is surprisingly well-implemented.Originally, ther menus were rendered in 640x480, but with a new update, the menus have now been vastly improved with much nicer graphics and fon, not that the menus actually looked any worse with the old resolution. As for the ""remastered"" sound effects, I really quite like them, they sound a lot nicer than WWP's original sound effects, and if you turn them off you've basically just got the original Worms World Party."
